        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 6:08PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 608 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Segundo, or 22 miles southwest of Trinidad, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern Las
Animas County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM MDT for
southeastern Colorado.</instruction>
